# NG-SENTRA Cloud Deployment Plan

## The Core Problem

Your NG-SENTRA dashboard is not just a website — it's a **SOC command center** that actively connects to local infrastructure:

| Feature | Connects To | Protocol |
|---|---|---|
| **SSH Terminal** | VirtualBox VM (`192.168.1.14:22`) | SSH/WebSocket |
| **AI Health Checks** | Systemd services & Docker containers on VM | SSH |
| **Wazuh Threat Feed** | Elasticsearch on VM (`192.168.1.14:9200`) | HTTPS |
| **Security Scanner** | Targets on your local network | TCP/UDP |
| **Database** | TiDB Cloud (public internet) | MySQL/TLS |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **The fundamental challenge:** Cloud servers (Vercel, Render, AWS) **cannot reach `192.168.1.14`** — it's a private IP that only exists on your home network. Any cloud-hosted backend would lose SSH, Wazuh, AI health checks, and the terminal.

The **only service** that works from the cloud is TiDB (your database), because it has a public URL.

