## Option B: Split Architecture (Frontend on Vercel + Backend Local)

If you prefer having the frontend "truly" on the cloud:

- Deploy **only the React frontend** to Vercel as a static site
- Run the **backend** locally with a Cloudflare Tunnel
- Configure the frontend to call the tunneled backend URL

> [!WARNING]
> This adds complexity: you need CORS configuration, separate build processes, and the frontend must be configured with the tunnel URL at build time. Option A is simpler and achieves the same result.

---

## Option C: Full Cloud VPS (Future — When Budget Available)

When you eventually have budget, the ideal production setup would be:

1. **VPS** (Hetzner €3.79/mo or DigitalOcean $6/mo) running NG-SENTRA
2. **WireGuard VPN** tunnel from VPS → your home network
3. Backend accesses `192.168.1.14` through the VPN tunnel
4. Everything is always-on 24/7

This is the most robust but requires a credit card and VPN configuration.

